replies.body:
ADC's buy {{item:3085}} because:

1. They have special interactions with it: {{champion:22}} {{champion:51}} {{champion:222}} {{champion:29}} 
2. They have a lot of on hit effects and/or easier stacking from passives etc.. or {{item:3124}}  : {{champion:96}} {{champion:10}} {{champion:203}} {{champion:85}} 
3. They can use an extra benefit from it (e.g. Lifesteal.) : {{champion:110}} {{champion:67}} {{champion:18}} 

NOT every ADC Buys {{item:3085}} , because :

1. They can use the attack speed from {{item:3046}}  better:  {{champion:67}}{{champion:119}}  {{champion:15}} {{champion:157}} 
2. They just can't use the {{item:3085}} passive properly: {{champion:104}} {{champion:236}}{{champion:119}}  {{champion:15}} {{champion:42}} 
3. They don't use zeal items : {{champion:21}} {{champion:133}} {{champion:202}}  {{champion:81}} {{champion:110}} 

**NOTE I**

Some Champions are in different categories because more reasons apply to them or it depends on the playstyle.

**NOTE II**

{{champion:67}} with {{item:3085}} was played for the interaction with lifesteal, to survive early game better, however it is not so common now, especially since they changed warlords.
{{champion:110}} has a crit and lethality build, but the crit build is more common now.

I hope this helped :-)

The ideal build for an ADC would be somewhat like this:

Start : {{item:1055}} {{item:2003}} 
First back : {{item:1038}} {{item:1001}} 
2nd back:  {{item:3086}} If not bought yet  {{item:1001}} 
First item: {{item:3085}} {{item:3046}} {{item:3094}} {{item:3087}} Depending on what your champion wants
2nd item: {{item:3031}} 
3rd Item:{{item:3006}} 

Then it depends, You could get another zeal item, or buy {{item:3072}} 
If the enemy has a lot of armor you buy {{item:3035}} 
If they have a lot of healing {{champion:8}} {{champion:106}}  {{champion:5}} {{champion:16}} {{champion:50}} {{champion:114}} {{champion:9}} etc... buy {{item:3123}} 
You can buy {{item:3035}} or {{item:3123}} whenever it's necessary after your first 2 items.

Normally you get 2 zeal items, 1 lifesteal item, infinity and last whisper.
However if you need some defense you can buy {{item:3156}} {{item:3139}} {{item:3026}} instead of a second zeal item
You can buy {{item:3022}} too, for better kiting against champions like {{champion:75}} {{champion:122}} {{champion:82}} {{champion:106}} while getting more hp. But it isn't in the best spot right now


Late game you can sell your boots for:

 A third zeal item
 A defensive item, if you don't have it already
Versus full ad compositions, or very ad heavy: {{item:3742}} This is what I do, but I'm not sure if it's the best you can buy.

**NOTE**
Some Champions like to get {{item:3508}}, it's not in the best spot atm, but {{champion:15}} {{champion:202}} {{champion:22}} sometimes buy it, you then get it after your boots, instead of your 2nd zeal item, or instead of infinity edge and then buy infinity edge after boots.
Also I recommend going Ferocity instead of warlords since it's only good on a few champions since it got changed, and if you want to carry you could really use the extra damage.
This is for Critical strike builds, Not for lethality users!

Hope this helped, if you don't understand something, or disagree you can always comment :)
